"{\"uid\": \"globalnews.ca-news-10645575-paris-2024-olympics-mascot-what-is-a-phryges\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Instructions:  Want to discuss?\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 31, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please read ourCommenting Policyfirst.\", \"from\": 32, \"to\": 70, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you get Global News from Instagram or Facebook - that will be changing.Find out how you can still connect with us.\", \"from\": 72, \"to\": 189, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 83, \"end\": 94, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Global_News\", \"score\": 0.9999992524033653, \"rank\": 7.475969805738691e-07, \"text\": \"Global News\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Global_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Global_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The2024 Paris Olympicsare finally upon us, and there is one pretty prominent symbol for these games that has a lot of people scratching their heads.\", \"from\": 191, \"to\": 339, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 199, \"end\": 204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6529529166060228e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The two red blobs that make up this year's iteration of the Summer Olympics'mascotslook more like they belong in a geometry class than on a sporting field, but they are actually a pretty important part of French history.\", \"from\": 341, \"to\": 561, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 546, \"end\": 560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French history\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No, thePhryges, as they are called, are not a pair of triangles, nor are they tongues or any other part of the body - instead, they are meant to represent a pair of Phrygian caps, a type of hat that is symbolic of the French liberation.\", \"from\": 563, \"to\": 799, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 728, \"end\": 736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"score\": 0.9999999607985054, \"rank\": 3.9201541692170236e-08, \"text\": \"Phrygian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\"}, {\"begin\": 781, \"end\": 787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9992917155442002, \"rank\": 0.0007084773264937387, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On vous pr\\u00e9sente la Phryge Olympique et la Phryge Paralympique !Les mascottes de#Paris2024\\u2728Sportives, f\\u00eatardes\\u2026 et fran\\u00e7aises \\ud83c\\uddeb\\ud83c\\uddf7  Here are the Olympic Phryge and the Paralympic Phryge!The#Paris2024mascots \\u2728They are sporty, love to party\\u2026 and are so French \\ud83c\\uddeb\\ud83c\\uddf7pic.twitter.com/plupKzQqNs  - Paris 2024 (@Paris2024)November 14, 2022    The Phryges(pronounced FREE-juh) are based on caps worn by 18th-century French revolutionaries who wore the head coverings as a symbol of freedom, but according to National Geographic, the origin of the capgoes back thousands of years, appearing in the Trojan War.\", \"from\": 801, \"to\": 1397, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1052, \"end\": 1058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9992917155442002, \"rank\": 0.0007084773264937387, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1209, \"end\": 1231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Revolution\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French revolutionaries\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Revolution\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Revolution\"}, {\"begin\": 1301, \"end\": 1320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Geographic\", \"score\": 0.9941780857625857, \"rank\": 0.00585600741044031, \"text\": \"National Geographic\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Geographic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Geographic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We chose the Phrygian cap because it's avery strong symbol for the French Republic,\\\" said Tony Estanguet, president of the Paris 2024 organizing committee, when the mascots were revealed.\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1587, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1417, \"end\": 1429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Phrygian cap\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\"}, {\"begin\": 1494, \"end\": 1508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}, {\"begin\": 1527, \"end\": 1537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.3672478791684285e-17, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"For French people, it's a very well-known object that is a symbol of freedom, an object that will represent mascots all across the world.\", \"from\": 1589, \"to\": 1727, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1598, \"end\": 1611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The fact that the Paralympics mascot has a visible disability also sends a strong message: to promote inclusion.\\\"\", \"from\": 1728, \"to\": 1841, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The caps, he added, are on \\\"a mission of revolution through sport.\\\"\", \"from\": 1843, \"to\": 1910, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Throughout French history, the caps have been worn.\", \"from\": 1912, \"to\": 1963, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1927, \"end\": 1941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French history\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They were donned when French revolutionaries stormed the Bastille prison in 1789, marking the beginning of the French Revolution during the construction of the Eiffel Tower and Notre-Dame de Paris Cathedral, and even at early iterations of the Olympic games.\", \"from\": 1964, \"to\": 2222, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1990, \"end\": 2012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Revolution\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French revolutionaries\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Revolution\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Revolution\"}, {\"begin\": 2025, \"end\": 2033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Storming_of_the_Bastille\", \"score\": 0.9968463814762426, \"rank\": 0.0031635952961230128, \"text\": \"Bastille\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Storming_of_the_Bastille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Storming_of_the_Bastille\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic Phryge and the Paralympic Phryge are taking the lead of a tribe which always has its trainers on \\ud83d\\udc5fWhat could be better than little Phrygian caps to lead the revolution through sport and accompany us to the#Paris2024Games!pic.twitter.com/hUjFI09zZM  - Paris 2024 (@Paris2024)November 14, 2022    Even today, Phrygian caps find their place in French art and society, being worn by protestors, appearing on French stamps and currency, and appearing in a part of the country's national school curriculum.\", \"from\": 2224, \"to\": 2736, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2212, \"end\": 2225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999429401231, \"rank\": 4.8240330383016017e-08, \"text\": \"Olympic games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 2372, \"end\": 2380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"score\": 0.9999999607985054, \"rank\": 3.9201541692170236e-08, \"text\": \"Phrygian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\"}, {\"begin\": 2548, \"end\": 2556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"score\": 0.9999999607985054, \"rank\": 3.9201541692170236e-08, \"text\": \"Phrygian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phrygian_cap\"}, {\"begin\": 2582, \"end\": 2588, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9992917155442002, \"rank\": 0.0007084773264937387, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2645, \"end\": 2651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9992917155442002, \"rank\": 0.0007084773264937387, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organizers have described the Olympic and Paralympic Phryges as belonging to a larger family.\", \"from\": 2738, \"to\": 2831, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They are thetwo main characters in a large tribe; they are part of the family of Phryges,\\\" Paris 2024 brand director Julie Matikhine said, according to Olympics.com.\", \"from\": 2833, \"to\": 2999, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2991, \"end\": 3003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999981398335896, \"rank\": 1.8601699084331831e-06, \"text\": \"Olympics.com\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"According to our narrative, they have existed for thousands of years and were present during several key events in French history.\\\"\", \"from\": 3000, \"to\": 3132, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3121, \"end\": 3135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French history\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She continued: \\\"Now they have returned for this big event in France to lead a mission of revolution through sport.\", \"from\": 3134, \"to\": 3248, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3200, \"end\": 3206, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999996532547503, \"rank\": 3.1569132007774096e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The aim is to show that sport can change everything in society.\", \"from\": 3249, \"to\": 3312, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The objective is to show that sport and its values can do great things.\", \"from\": 3313, \"to\": 3384, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's about fraternity, solidarity and it helps society grow.\\\"\", \"from\": 3385, \"to\": 3446, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And while the two mascots look quite similar, they have been assigned opposite but complementary personalities.\", \"from\": 3448, \"to\": 3559, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic Phryge \\\"is a tactician with a calculating, mathematical brain.\", \"from\": 3561, \"to\": 3635, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Its methodical mind and alluring charm are sure to inspire people to get involved with sport.\\\"\", \"from\": 3636, \"to\": 3730, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, the Paralympic Phryge, who has a prosthetic leg and racing blade, \\\"is spontaneous and full of energy and enthusiasm.\\\"\", \"from\": 3731, \"to\": 3859, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Together, their motto is: \\\"Alone we go faster, but together we go further.\\\"\", \"from\": 3861, \"to\": 3936, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The email you need for the day's top news stories from Canada and around the world.\", \"from\": 3938, \"to\": 4021, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3998, \"end\": 4004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999919446069484, \"rank\": 5.355458305543495e-06, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The email you need for the day's top news stories from Canada and around the world.\", \"from\": 4023, \"to\": 4106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4083, \"end\": 4089, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999919446069484, \"rank\": 5.355458305543495e-06, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}]}"